0.  WHICH LICENSE BINDS YOU
================================================================================

    Read carefully.  The two licenses are NOT alternative grants of equal
    weight; the SCSL-1.0 is the master document, and the AGPL-3.0 is preserved
    as a regulatory fallback for two specific situations only:

    (i)  After the SCSL-1.0 "Change Date" (four (4) years from the first public
         availability of any given Release on the canonical Spektre Labs source
         of truth), that Release is automatically and unconditionally
         re-licensed under the AGPL-3.0-only — see SCSL-1.0 §12 ("Change Date
         and Conversion to Open Source").  A rolling, always-eventually-free
         four-year window is in effect.

    (ii) For any portion of the Software that is a derivative of, or that
         incorporates, third-party AGPL-3.0-licensed code, the AGPL-3.0
         applies to that portion as a co-license, in addition to the SCSL-1.0.

    For ALL OTHER USE — including without limitation any Commercial Use as
    defined in SCSL-1.0 §1.8 — only the SCSL-1.0 binds You, and that License
    REQUIRES You to obtain a separate paid Commercial License under §4 of the
    SCSL-1.0 before any Commercial Use is permitted.

